thread.title: Slayers to defend high school angling crown
thread.title_full: Slayers to defend high school angling crown

author: msawyers@times-news.com(Michael A Sawyers)
title: Slayers to defend high school angling crown
text:
by Michael A Sawyers 
OAKLAND â€” Morgan Winegardner and Joe McClosky, members of the Southern Garrett Bass Slayers, will be on the lower Potomac River Sunday defending their title as the best high school bass angling team in Maryland. 
The state bass tournament for high school teams will be hosted by Maryland Bass Nation at Smallwood State Park. The one-day tournament has a weigh-in at 3 p.m. 
Tournament updates will be available on the Southern Garrett Bass Slayers Facebook page. 
Winegardner and McClosky won the 2014 high school tournament and then competed in the national championship at Kentucky Lake this past summer, but did not finish in the prizes. 
The club will send five other angling teams as well. The team of Ryan Roszell and Justin Peck placed 6th in the 2014 Maryland tournament. Trent Lohr and Troy Cumerlato finished 8th. Competing for the first time will be the teams of Michael Mayles and J.T. Mullins, Quinn Iden and Zachary Warnick, and Devan Hamrick and Austin Smith.
